{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"24fa7bca-236f-4843-97d1-acb70cc5f11f","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from knowledge:\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default** — `UseVSTest` was opting you back into the legacy runner.\n2. **CLI changes** — run tests with `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test executable directly (`./YourTests.exe`).\n3. **`dotnet test` compatibility** — add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` if `dotnet test` integration isn't working smoothly (needed in some older SDK versions).\n4. **Remove** any explicit `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference — MSTest.Sdk handles this.\n5. **Runsettings** — some `.runsettings` options don't apply; platform-specific configuration uses CLI args or `testconfig.json` instead.\n\nThat single property removal is the core change. Rebuild and run `dotnet test` to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6f2d5a71-b796-46a3-9af3-884294099813","outputTokens":392,"requestId":"BC26:63E52:1CAD6BA:1FBEA4A:69FA905C"},"id":"5b4ce374-c545-44ae-b187-a96771de5fb4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:47.570Z","parentId":"e38e1d07-df68-4050-a0d8-b3caf46d42c9"}
